# Testing Standards

## Coverage
- Track coverage with `go test -cover -tags sqlite_fts5 ./...`
- All new code must have tests; target 100% line coverage on new packages.
- Use `go tool cover -html=coverage.out` to find uncovered lines.
- Build tag `sqlite_fts5` is required for all test commands.

## Test Structure
- Table-driven tests for functions with multiple input/output cases.
- Each `foo.go` has a corresponding `foo_test.go` in the same package.
- Helpers shared across tests go in `testutil_test.go`.

## Mocking & Isolation
- Database: use in-memory SQLite (`file::memory:?cache=shared`) seeded with known fixtures.
- HTTP (REST API): use `net/http/httptest.NewServer` with handler stubs.
- WhatsApp client: do **not** call real WhatsApp APIs in tests; wrap access behind interfaces and provide test doubles.
- File system: use `t.TempDir()` for any file I/O.

## E2E MCP Tests
- Instantiate `server.MCPServer`, call `server.ServeStdio`-style helpers or invoke tool handlers directly.
- Assert on JSON tool results, not internal types.
- Cover every registered MCP tool with at least one success and one error case.

## Naming
- Test functions: `TestFunctionName_scenario` (e.g. `TestListChats_fuzzyMatch`).
- Sub-tests via `t.Run("description", ...)`.

## Running
```bash
./tasks.sh test        # run all tests with coverage summary
./tasks.sh test-cover  # open HTML coverage report
```
